Confirm Let's Encrypt challenge data is ready.

Remove an enrollment.

Removes an enrollment from the CPS. The response type will vary depending on the state of the enrollment. Deleting an enrollment in the future or when the enrollment has a certificate deployed to the network may return HTTP Status 202 (Accepted). Deleting an enrollment which hasn't deployed a certificate to the network yet will complete immediately and return HTTP Status 200 (OK).

Force certificate renewal for Enrollment.

CPS will automatically start a Change to renew certificates in time before they expire. This automatic Change is started when Certificate's expiration is within a renewal window, and system will protect against other changes started during this renewal window. Setting renewal-date-check-override=true will allow creating a Change during the renewal window, potentially running the risk of ending up with an expired certificate on the network.
